  <groupId>net.sf.jpasecurity</groupId>
  <artifactId>jpasecurity</artifactId>
  <name>JPA Security</name>
  <version>${version}</version>
  <description>
    JPA Security is an Access Control Solution for the Java Persistence API. 
    JPA Security provides an interface to define security requirements of your
    Data Access Layer via configuration (Annotations or XML). Thus JPA Security
    enables you to completely remove security-related code from your code-base,
    improving development and maintainability.
    JPA Security is designed to extend current security solutions like J2EE Security
    and Spring Security (formerly known as Acegi-Security),
    but may be used on its own, too. It enables you to configure access control
    to your JPA Entity Beans based on the currently authenticated user
    and/or its roles in the application.
  </description>
  <url>http://jpasecurity.sf.net</url>

